 murder, and abuse to false conviction, torture, and systemic racism, Goodman describes the daily experiences that both rattled his worldview and motivated him to work ever harder. Part memoir, part exposé, Everyone against Us is the moving story of an embattled civil servant who staves off the worst abuses of the criminal justice system, at great personal cost.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCriminal justice, Administration ofzIllinoiszCook County. 0aPublic defenderszIllinoiszCook CountyvBiography. 7aTRUE CRIME / General.2bisacsh  apublic defender, criminal justice, Chicago.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226826240423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226826240/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles